2020-05-29.text: I am not the same person i was a year ago nor would i ever want to be her again.

This past year I’ve grown as a person and realized how horrible it is to use words like that let alone find it humorous. i know it’s not fair to those who saw me as an activist/feminist and i truly hope that everyone who was hurt or affected by my post in any way can forgive me.

This is not an excuse but if something like this is going to cause me to receive Death Threats and have my personal information exposed then it’s only fair to share my side of this and the facts about the picture.

I knew then and i know now that it was wrong of me to say it, let alone make a joke out of it. I want to sincerely apologize for using such a disgusting word that perpetuates the issues in our society. 
That being said those pictures were taken over a year ago.

To the ones that I have offended and hurt. Yesterday two offensive images i had posted in the past, to be precise almost a 1 year and a half ago, were brought to twitter. I do not have an excuse for the racial slurs that were used in the caption of both pictures.
